 xp. I dropped it down to 90% and gained about half a blue bubble over the next 10 kills. So it seems to be bugged. I bugged it on Test as well. <p>Shinku Kiri<br>
Assassin</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukarak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Karak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/12/02 1:48:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23274.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AA xps at 100% bugged!</span><hr size=1> The ONLY way to definitively tell is to set your aaxp at 10%, and count the number of mobs it takes to get a full yellow, then set aaxp to 20, repeat, etc.<br>
<br>
It is very important in this test that a) you remain the same level.  b) Your group remains the same size.  c) you remain in the same camp killing the same mobs.<br>
<br>
If you want to go anecdotally; wednesday night while pulling howling stones, I pulled thirty mobs to an AE group, killed them all, and my aaxp didn't budge.  The VERY NEXT PULL was only 7 mobs, and my aaxp went up a blue.  There was no change in group size, there was no change in where I had my aaxp slider. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ushiba.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shiba</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/12/02 3:16:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23274.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AA xps at 100% bugged!</span><hr size=1> They admitted there was a problem with this about three patches ago.  Its &quot;being looked in to&quot; is the way they phrased it.   Tried to find a link to the statement Alan made, can't seem to locate it. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ushiba.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shiba</A> at: 4/12/02 3:17:07 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unexc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nexc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/12/02 3:26:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23274.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AA xps at 100% bugged!</span><hr size=1> Just as a sidenote, I had barely seen blue move at all after two kills with 100% in, being curious, I put it to 90%, and after two more kills I had gained over half a blue.<br>
<br>
I am not sure if this is zone specific or not.<br>
<br>
Loch, Assassin of Twist of Fate, Innoruuk.<br>
